@Reasoning
Release of map handle - decrements all the refcounts in the subtree
and frees nodes whose count reaches zero. Caller still must release
the header itself.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Iterative traversal with a node stack. Decrement each node's refcount;
if reaches zero, push children if BITMAP/COLLISION and then free.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) worst case for unique structure.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller-owned.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pmap_destroy" takes pm as Integer returns Integer:
    If pm is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let root be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with pm, 0
    Let cap be 64
    Let buf_bytes be cap multiplied by 8
    Let buf be proc allocate from Layout with buf_bytes
    If buf is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with pm
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sp be 0
    If root is not equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with buf, 0, root
        Set sp to 1
    End If
    While sp is greater than 0:
        Set sp to sp minus 1
        Let off be sp multiplied by 8
        Let node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with buf, off
        Let rc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 16
        Let new_rc be rc minus 1
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 16, new_rc
        If new_rc is equal to 0:
            Let tag be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 0
            If tag is equal to PMAP_TAG_BITMAP:
                Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 24
                Let i be 0
                While i is less than child_count:
                    Let child_addr be node plus (32 plus (i multiplied by 8))
                    Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with child_addr, 0
                    Let need be sp plus 1
                    If need is greater than cap:
                        Let new_cap be cap multiplied by 2
                        Let new_bytes be new_cap multiplied by 8
                        Let new_buf be proc allocate from Layout with new_bytes
                        If new_buf is equal to 0:
                            proc deallocate from Layout with buf
                            proc deallocate from Layout with pm
                            Return 0
                        End If
                        Let copy_bytes be cap multiplied by 8
                        proc memory_copy from Memory with new_buf, buf, copy_bytes
                        proc deallocate from Layout with buf
                        Set buf to new_buf
                        Set cap to new_cap
                    End If
                    Let s_off be sp multiplied by 8
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with buf, s_off, child
                    Set sp to sp plus 1
                    Set i to i plus 1
                End While
            End If
            proc deallocate from Layout with node
        End If
    End While
    proc deallocate from Layout with buf
    proc deallocate from Layout with pm
    Return 1
End Process
